{"rightSidebarLinks":[{"id":"authorization-resolver","title":"authorization-resolver","subLink":null},{"id":"authorizationroutes","title":"Authorization Routes","subLink":[]}],"title":"Authorization Resolver","description":"","validatorType":"template-driven","validationTypeTitle":"Template Driven Decorator","type":"simple","gitDocPath":"https://github.com/rxweb/rxweb.io/edit/master/docs/angular/learn/authorization-resolver.md","category":"learn","subCategory":null,"linkTitle":"authorization-resolver","tabArray":{},"innerHtml":null,"htmlContent":"<div class='row page-section' id= 'authorizationroutes'>\r\n<div class='col-lg-12'>\r\n<h2>Authorization Routes<a title='Link to this heading' class='link-header' href='/learn/authorization-resolver/template-driven/decorators#authorizationroutes'><i class='fa fa-link'></i></a></h2>\r\n\r\n<p class='showHideElement' >Authorizing routes include navigating the user along with retrieval of the user accesses whenever the particular route is called. This will be achieved by following   </p>\r\n<p class='showHideElement' >these steps</p>\r\n<p class='showHideElement' >1) Creating the <span class='highlighted'>Authorization</span> class for retrieving the user roles</p>\r\n<div component=\"app-code\" key=\"authorization-resolver-add-component\"></div> \r\n<p class='showHideElement' >2) Registering it globally into the app module using <span class='highlighted'>@routerModule</span></p>\r\n<div component=\"app-code\" key=\"authorization-resolver-add-component\"></div> \r\n<p class='showHideElement' >3) Using <span class='highlighted'>@access</span> into the component</p>\r\n<div component=\"app-code\" key=\"authorization-resolver-add-function\"></div> \r\n<p class='showHideElement' >4)  Using <span class='highlighted'>BaseCanActivate</span> into the routes</p>\r\n<div component=\"app-code\" key=\"authorization-resolver-add-html\"></div>\r\n</div></div>\r\n"}